    <detaileddescription>
<para>Interactions are a unified way provided by Discord to handle <ref refid="slashcommands" kindref="compound">slash commands</ref> and <ref refid="components-menu" kindref="compound">component interactions</ref>, such as <ref refid="components" kindref="compound">clicking a button</ref>. Slash commands are much better than message commands as they are not rate limited as much, meaning your bot can handle a lot more at once. They also contain a lot of data about a command, for example by making a command take a user as a parameter, <ref refid="resolved-objects" kindref="compound">the entire user object will be contained in the interaction</ref> so you do not have to fetch it yourself, avoiding even more rate limits!</para>
